race.comment: ZOUCRATIC (5) registered his maiden win last time out at the fourth attempt, getting home by half a length over 1250m at Newcastle. Only third-up today so don't expect him to be going backwards at this stage. Bjorn Baker's VIKTOR (2) is back from a six-month break. Closed last prep with a big win over this trip in a Mudgee maiden of questionable quality. Trialled twice so should be up for this. VALIANT BOMB (7) settled just off the speed then worked home well for third when resuming over 1250m at Newcastle recently. Genuine four-year-old who scored easily at this stage last prep. Right in contention. STORM SEASON (1) resumes. Opened last prep with a win over today's journey at Pakenham so must be respected. INSAIN JEWEL (9) has not appeared since her win on debut at Nowra in June. Betting will be crucial.
